name: NewbornAffectedByPlacentaOrAbruptionS
title: Newborn Affected by Placenta or Abruption S
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains diagnoses most commonly used for newborns with placenta previa or abruption.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify newborns who have an active  diagnosis of placenta previa or abruption. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Diagnosis" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Codes representing the SNOMED-CT code system for the diagnosis of placenta previa or abruption.),(Exclusion Criteria: None.)
